CatDescriptText: Mr. William Fletcher, State interviewer and investigator, Homestead was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 14, 1960, pg. A1 with question: "In your opinion what political party has done the most for the Negroes?"  Answer reads: "Both parties are about equal in considering who has done the most for the Negro...However, I don't think either party is going out of its way to especially help the Negro."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of William Fletcher wearing dark suit, standing in front of Brass Rail Restaurant, B/G, and Quality Insurance signs, Smithfield Street, Downtown
